ParticleEmitter.name: ParticleEmitter
ParticleEmitter.description:
A Particle Emitter extends DisplayObject and must be added to a Container object. An emitter will emit a stream of particles
adhereing to the given configuration.

params.name: image
params.description: The image to use for each particle. If no image is provided then a simple circle will be drawn.

classitems.description: Enum to represent the state of the particle emitter
Enum to represent the type of the particle emitter
Should the emitter be removed from the parent when finished?
classitems.name: autoRemoveOnFinished

classitems.description: Is debug mode active for this emitter. If so, render debug text.
classitems.name: debugMode

classitems.description:
The amount of time (milliseconds) that the emitter will last. A value of -1 means that the emitter will 
last for an infinite amount of time.
classitems.name: duration

classitems.description: The type of particle emitter to create
classitems.name: emitterType

classitems.description: The total number of particles that can exist at any one time
classitems.name: maxParticles

classitems.description: The rate at which particles are generated (number of particles per second)
classitems.name: emissionRate

classitems.description: The current state of the particle emitter
classitems.name: state

classitems.description: The image to show for each particle
classitems.name: image

classitems.description: The accelerration of each particle in the X axis.
classitems.name: accelerationX

classitems.description: The accelerration of each particle in the Y axis. This can be used to simulate forces such as Gravity
classitems.name: accelerationY

classitems.description: The angle (degrees) in which to fire the particle from the origin point
classitems.name: angle

classitems.description: The amount of degrees that the angle can vary by
classitems.name: angleVar

classitems.description:
The end opacity of each particle, where 1 is opaque and 0 is transparent. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endOpacity

classitems.description:
The end color of each particle [r,g,b]. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endColor

classitems.description:
The variance in the end color. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endColorVar

classitems.description:
The end size of each particle, in pixels. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endSize

classitems.description:
The variance in end size, in pixels. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endSizeVar

classitems.description:
The number of degrees to spin each particle per second when each particle is destroyed. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endSpin

classitems.description:
The variance in end spin. A null value signifies that
the value will not differ from the start value.
classitems.name: endSpinVar

classitems.description: The amount of time (milliseconds) that each particle will last before being destroyed
classitems.name: life

classitems.description: The variance in the amount of life time (milliseconds)
classitems.name: lifeVar

classitems.description: The variance in the x position of emitted particles
classitems.name: positionVarX

classitems.description: The variance in the y position of emitted particles
classitems.name: positionVarY

classitems.description: The radial acceleration of the particle
classitems.name: radialAcceleration

classitems.description: The variance of the radial acceleration of the particle
classitems.name: radialAccelerationVar

classitems.description: The number of pixels per second that the particle will move
classitems.name: speed

classitems.description: The number of pixels per second that the speed can vary by
classitems.name: speedVar

classitems.description: The start opacity of each particle, where 1 is opaque and 0 is transparent
classitems.name: startOpacity

classitems.description: The color of each particle [r,g,b] when it is created
classitems.name: startColor

classitems.description: The variance in the start color
classitems.name: startColorVar

classitems.description: The start size of each particle, in pixels
classitems.name: startSize

classitems.description: The variance in start size, in pixels
classitems.name: startSizeVar

classitems.description: The number of degrees to spin each particle per second when each particle is created
classitems.name: startSpin

classitems.description: The variance in start spin
classitems.name: startSpinVar

classitems.description: The tangental acceleration of the particle
classitems.name: tangentalAcceleration

classitems.description: The variance in the tangental acceleration of the particle
classitems.name: tangentalAccelerationVar

classitems.description: Resets the emitter which removes any active particles before starting all over again.
classitems.name: reset
